The Federal Government has unveiled plans to engage 17, 000 youths in rabbit farming, to develop the rabbit rearing in the country.
 
Executive Secretary of the National Agricultural Land Development Authority (NALDA), Paul Ikonne during a press briefing in Abuja, disclosed that the agency designed the project to engage youths in the Southern part of the country on rabbit rearing.
 
He said the beneficiaries would not only be trained and empowered, but would also be taught on how they can harvest the urine and pooh of rabbits (for fertilizer purposes), from which they can earn a minimum of N100,000 monthly. Ikonne explained that the first phase of the programme had commenced in Abia, Imo and Oyo states, saying the aim was to implement the project across 18 states.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .